issues.title: AMG GT Engine Oil Leaks from Valve Cover Gaskets
issues.description: Multiple reports of oil leaks developing from valve cover gaskets on the M178 4.0L twin-turbo V8 engine, particularly affecting early production models. Oil can leak onto hot exhaust components creating fire risk.
issues.fix_description: Replace valve cover gaskets and associated seals, clean affected areas
issues.prevention: Regular oil change intervals, inspect engine bay regularly for leaks

issues.title: Transmission Harsh Shifting and Jerking
issues.description: AMG Speedshift DCT 7-speed dual-clutch transmission experiencing harsh shifts, jerking during acceleration, and delayed engagement. Software updates and clutch replacements often required.
issues.fix_description: Software update, transmission fluid change, or clutch pack replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Allow transmission to warm up, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: Common rattling noise from turbocharger wastegate actuators, particularly noticeable during cold starts and light acceleration. Can lead to reduced performance if left unaddressed.
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger wastegate actuator or entire turbocharger unit
issues.prevention: Allow engine to warm up properly, use high-quality engine oil

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Roof Panel Cracking
issues.description: Reports of carbon fiber roof panels developing stress cracks, particularly around mounting points. More common in vehicles exposed to extreme temperature variations.
issues.fix_description: Replace carbon fiber roof panel, inspect mounting hardware
issues.prevention: Avoid parking in direct sunlight for extended periods, use car cover

issues.title: Air Suspension Compressor Failure
issues.description: AMG Ride Control air suspension compressor failures causing vehicle to sag or become inoperable. Common on vehicles with higher mileage or frequent track use.
issues.fix_description: Replace air suspension compressor and check air lines for leaks
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of air lines, avoid overloading vehicle

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Rebooting
issues.description: COMAND infotainment system experiencing random freezes, black screens, and automatic reboots. Software glitches affecting navigation, audio, and vehicle settings.
issues.fix_description: Software update or head unit replacement if hardware failure
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid using while engine is starting

issues.title: Brake Disc Warping and Premature Wear
issues.description: Front brake discs developing warping and excessive wear, particularly on track-driven vehicles. AMG ceramic brakes also showing premature wear issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake discs and pads, inspect brake fluid for contamination
issues.prevention: Proper brake cooling after track use, quality brake fluid changes

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Electronic door handles experiencing mechanical failures, preventing door opening from inside or outside. More common in earlier production models.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism and actuator
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, regular lubrication

issues.title: Battery Drain and Electrical Issues
issues.description: Parasitic battery drain causing dead batteries, particularly after short-term parking. Various electrical modules staying active when vehicle is off.
issues.fix_description: Diagnose electrical drain, update software, replace faulty modules
issues.prevention: Use battery tender for long-term storage, regular electrical system checks

issues.title: Exhaust System Component Failure
issues.description: AMG Performance exhaust system components including valves and actuators failing, affecting exhaust note and performance. Particularly affects vehicles with active exhaust systems.
issues.fix_description: Replace exhaust valve actuators or control modules
issues.prevention: Regular exhaust system inspection, avoid water submersion

editorial.tagline: AMG's purest sports car expression meets twin-turbo fury
editorial.hero_blurb: The Mercedes-AMG GT represents AMG's most focused sports car effort, delivering raw performance wrapped in stunning design. Born from the SLS's DNA but with modern twin-turbo efficiency, it's a proper supercar slayer that doesn't compromise on daily usability.
editorial.essence: This is AMG's answer to Porsche's 911, but with distinctly German muscle car attitude. The hand-built M178 engine and rear-biased dynamics create a driving experience that's both visceral and sophisticated.
editorial.heritage: Launched in 2015 as AMG's second standalone sports car after the SLS, the GT carries forward the long-hood, rear-transaxle formula while introducing AMG's new twin-turbo era. It represents the transition from naturally aspirated drama to forced-induction efficiency without losing soul.
editorial.design_philosophy: Long hood, short deck proportions with aggressive functional aerodynamics. Every line serves performance, from the wide haunches housing massive tires to the active rear spoiler that deploys at speed.
editorial.motorsport_history: Spawned the GT3 and GT4 race cars that dominate global motorsport series. The road car directly benefits from track-developed aerodynamics and suspension geometry proven in competition.
editorial.engine_character: The M178 4.0L twin-turbo V8 is hand-assembled fury incarnate. Despite the turbos, it revs eagerly to redline with building intensity, delivering massive torque from low revs while maintaining high-rpm excitement.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7-speed dual-clutch fires off lightning-fast shifts in Race mode, yet remains smooth enough for traffic. Manual mode gives complete control over the aggressive shift programming.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Rear-biased all-wheel drive in S models, pure rear-drive in base GT. The transaxle layout provides perfect weight distribution, while adaptive dampers can transform from comfort cruiser to track weapon instantly.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulically-assisted rack delivers old-school feedback with modern precision. Weight builds naturally with speed, providing clear communication about grip levels and road surface changes.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo brakes with incredible stopping power and fade resistance. Pedal feel is firm and progressive, inspiring confidence during hard track sessions or spirited mountain drives.
editorial.sound_signature: Deep, rumbling idle transforms into a thunderous roar under acceleration. The active exhaust system can whisper for neighbors or wake the dead, with authentic V8 pops and crackles on overrun.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance enthusiasts who want Porsche-rivaling dynamics with distinctive German muscle character. Perfect for drivers who appreciate hand-built engines and aren't afraid of maintenance costs.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking maximum practicality or budget-conscious ownership. The rear seats are useless for adults, and AMG maintenance intervals require dedication and deep pockets.
editorial.buyers_summary: Find the best-maintained example possible, as these engines and transmissions demand proper care. The S model's all-wheel drive adds capability but the base GT's rear-drive purity is intoxicating for purists.
pros: Hand-built twin-turbo V8 with incredible sound
cons: Transmission can be jerky at low speeds
